In 2000 he moved to Valle and, after completing the required courses, specialized in laphoscopy, which is the examination of the skin exposed to friction, i.e. the hands and feet.
In the week of deployment against the so-called Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was instructed to pack clothes for at least three days.
Something big awaited him.
On Friday night he flew a helicopter from Palmira to Cauca.
He knew that he should identify two bodies, and that one was suspected to be that of the man who had led the oldest guerrilla in the world.
However, when he reached the place where the body was, he could not identify him because of his physical appearance, because it was not at all similar to the images he had seen in the mass media.
He had no beard, was dressed like a farmer in the area, wore no glasses and was much thinner.
Fingerprints do not lie.
Armed with a lamp, ink, a plant cell and a pocket lamp, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those on the printing sheet.
He had seen right: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, this man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for informing Defense Minister Juan Carlos Pinzón that he was actually the leader of the FARC.
In search of traces
For a Dactyloscope from Sijín in Cali, the recognition given by President Juan Manuel Santos Eliazar González at a press conference on the use against "Cano" was very important.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science with no error rate that can be a key factor in resolving a crime.
Lophoscopists not only identify bodies, they also support investigations in murder and robbery cases and confirm the identities of the arrested persons.
When they are arrested, many offenders present false identity documents or they have none.
We take your fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher told us that in a theft he had to tear a piece of wall out of a house because the thief had stood up with his hand right there as he pulled out a safe filled with jewelry and money.
"Walls are difficult because their surfaces are unsuitable for fingerprinting, but in this case we were able to take the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in several thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also be used to relieve or burden murder suspects.
Recently, a dead man was found surrounded by bottles.
During the investigation, it was suspected that a family member could be the suspect, and actually a fingerprint on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that he is the murderer, he is still linked to the place where the crime was committed.
A Dactyloscopist at the CTI explained that "fingerprints were taken from the object with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a plant cell or tape is used to take.
After that, the fingerprints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Personal Status Office.
“The problem is that there are still many Colombians without passports,” the CTI expert said.
