Austria also fulfils a demand from the Brussels summit of the eurozone member states on 26 October: The heads of state and government then demanded the inclusion of the reduction of public deficits by the end of 2012 and a return to the balance of public accounts in the constitution or by passing an equivalent law.
The measure taken by the Austrian government in this regard is similar to the "German model", since Germany was the first European country to include such a "rule" in the constitution.
By 2017, the structural budget deficit should be reduced by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year, from 2017 the structural budget deficit of the state should not exceed the 0.35% limit of GDP, while regional states and municipalities should have balanced budgets.
The goal is to eradicate budgetary debt by 2020/21 below the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Agreement.
